text: Vézelin-sur-Loire is a commune in the Loire department in central France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint- Paul-de-Vézelin (the seat), Amions and Dancé.Arrêté préfectoral 20 June 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Loire department ==References== * INSEE commune file Category:Communes of Loire (department)
title: Vézelin-sur-Loire
